1. Avatar Enhancement (User Profile Improvement)
Current Situation

The system currently provides a basic avatar template.

Same avatar style is used for all users.

Proposed Improvement

Introduce two different avatar sets:

Adult-style avatars → for Parents

Cute / child-friendly avatars → for Students

This improves user experience and better matches the preschool environment.

Default Avatar Handling

When creating a new Parent or Student account:

A default avatar is automatically assigned.

User can later change the avatar (if allowed by role).

Error Handling

If avatar upload fails → system assigns default avatar.

Invalid image format → show error message
“Invalid image type. Please upload JPG or PNG.”

2. Fee Reminder System (Access-Controlled Notifications)
Current Situation

Fee reminders exist but need stronger access control.

Proposed Improvement

Fee reminders should be visible only to the relevant parent.

Parents cannot view other parents’ fee reminders.

System Rules

Fee reminder is generated per student / per parent.

Parent dashboard shows:

Due month

Due amount

Payment status

Error Handling

If parent tries to access another parent’s reminder:

System blocks access

Displays:
“Unauthorized access detected.”

If no pending fees:

Show message:
“No pending payments.”

3. Menu & Access Restrictions (UI + Security)
Removal Actions

The following UI actions will be removed to avoid misuse:

❌ Remove Add Student option from sidebar

❌ Remove Add Parent option from sidebar

❌ Remove Edit button from Parent Details Dashboard

Reason

Student and Parent creation should be admin-only

Prevent accidental or unauthorized data changes

Error Handling

If a user accesses restricted URL directly:

Redirect to dashboard

Show message:
“You do not have permission to perform this action.”

4. Auditing & Activity Logging System
Purpose

To ensure accountability, security, and traceability of all system actions.

Activities to be Logged

Adding new records (student, parent, teacher)

Editing records

Deleting records

Payment verification

Report generation

Announcement and event creation

Audit Log Fields

User ID

User role (Admin / Teacher)

Action type

Date & time

Affected record ID

Example

Admin (ID: A102) updated Student Record (ID: S205) at 10:35 AM

Error Handling

If logging fails:

System continues operation

Error saved in system error log

Audit logs are read-only (cannot be edited or deleted)

5. Announcement System Enhancement
Current Limitation

Announcements can be sent to only one classroom.

Proposed Improvement

Allow announcements to be sent to:

Multiple classrooms

Entire preschool (global announcement)

Permission Rules

✅ Teachers → can create announcements

❌ Teachers → cannot delete announcements

✅ Only Super Admin can:

Delete announcements

Delete homework

Error Handling

If teacher attempts delete:

Show message:
“Only Super Admin can delete this content.”

6. Billing System Enhancements
6.1 Overdue & Pending Payment Handling

Add two new billing buckets in Overview Page:

🔴 Overdue Payments

🟡 Pending Approval Payments (uploaded but not verified)

Rules

Payments uploaded but not verified → go to Pending Approval

Past due date without payment → go to Overdue

6.2 Billing UI Improvements

Change button placement and colors:

Student Billing → Primary color

Expenses → Secondary color

Remove billing actions from Quick Actions

Dedicated Billing Page only

6.3 Monthly Payment Locking

If parent pays for January:

January payment button becomes disabled

Shows status: “Paid”

Prevents:

Duplicate payments

Accidental double uploads

Error Handling

If parent tries to pay again:

Show message:
“Payment already completed for this month.”

7. Event Management Enhancements
7.1 Event Creation with Approval Flow

Teachers can create events

Events require Super Admin approval before publishing

Status Flow

Draft → Pending Approval → Approved → Published

7.2 Event Data Improvements

❌ Remove Attendees column

✅ Add Event Media URL

Photo links

Video links (Google Drive / YouTube)

7.3 Classroom-Based Event Participation

New feature: Select which classrooms can attend

Event visible only to:

Assigned classrooms

Relevant parents

Error Handling

If parent opens non-eligible event:

Show message:
“This event is not assigned to your child’s classroom.”


